BrokenGallery

Target IP: 192.168.228.24

Scanning



There are two TCP ports open on the target machine: SSH and HTTP.

Enumeration

Port 80: HTTP

The webpage above is displayed for this application. It contains four images and two HTML pages. I read the source-code of the HTML pages and I did not find anything useful.


The page gallery.html displays the webpage above. It displays the four images with their names. I performed LFI tests and I could not find anything. I also performed directory search and I could not find anything. The only port left now is SSH.

Port 22: SSH

I created a wordlist with the name wordlist of the different names of the photos, and the machine name.


Using hydra, I performed the command hydra -L wordlist -P wordlist ssh://192.168.228.24 -t 4 and got a successful hit on the credential broken:broken, as shown above.

Exploitation


Now I have a SSH foothold on the machine as the user broken. I used the credential above to login as this user.

Privilege Escalation


Running sudo -l shows two interesting entries.


Spawning a root shell was super simple. I ran the command sudo /usr/bin/timedatectl list-timezones first. And then I used !/bin/sh to spawn a root shell. Now I have a root shell on the target machine.
